<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-08-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-08-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="559" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d559">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.124/303.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-08-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 18, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Government knows nothing of changes referred to by Ecuadorean
                            Minister. The matter has not been bought before Congress. Companies
                            mentioned bid about the time MacArthur. All bids must be made blindly,
                            as there is no contractor capable of preparing intelligent plan. Economy
                            or ability of Americans will not affect the award. I have received from
                            the Minister for Foreign Affairs a reply to my protest, saying that
                            nothing further will be done until the special commissioner now in
                            Europe seeking bids returns.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Schuyler</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>